commit.message: Add support for Razer Basilisk V3 X HyperSpeed

daemon: Fix DPI_MAX for Basilisk V3 Pro

The maximum DPI of this device is 30000 and not 26000.

Fixes #2194
Add support for Razer Cobra

Remove "None" effect for Basilisk V3

Setting the "None" effect causes this mouse to enter a buggy state.
If the computer was rebooted while the "None" is set, the mouse won't be
detected again until it is physically replugged.

Some users found that a firmware update solved it, while others reported
a factory reset (on Synapse) works. Ultimately, the firmware is stable
when none of the "None" effects are set.

Better to prevent this situation from happening by removing the effect.

Fixes #2049
Addresses #1767, #1844

driver: Fix effects on Naga Epic Chroma

Fixes: 7b8d48e2 ("Move Naga Epic Chroma to effect API in kernel")

Remove timestamp from manpages

openrazer-daemon is not reproducible in Arch Linux because the build
time gets appended in the header of the compressed manpages.

The recommended solution (see [1,2]) is to pass -n to gzip.

The package in Debian is reproducible because strip-nondeterminism is
run by default.

[1]: https://salsa.debian.org/reproducible-builds/reproducible-notes/-/blob/master/issues.yml
[2]: https://wiki.debian.org/ReproducibleBuilds/TimestampsInGzipHeaders

razerkbd: Don't ask for response for BlackWidow V4 Pro custom frame

Do not expect responses for `matrix_custom_frame` and
`matrix_effect_custom` commands. This is more similar to what Synapse
does on Windows and apparently eliminates matrix glitches when
continuously updating a custom effect.

See: https://github.com/openrazer/openrazer/pull/2054#issuecomment-1615283977
